History: History: M with chest pain, acute cardiopulm disease.
Findings: Again, there is diffuse increase in interstitial markings bilaterally consistent with chronic interstitial lung disease. No new areas of focal consolidation are seen. No pleural effusion or pneumothorax is seen. The cardiac and mediastinal silhouettes are stable.
Impression: No acute cardiopulmonary process. Chronic interstitial lung disease, stable since the prior study.
